            <Execution>
                Executed once per iteration of the periodic control loop (CMP--10), after sensor acquisition and map update, before motion output.
                Internal variables include:
                - mission_state ∈ {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - last_exploration_event_type ∈ {NONE, EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT}.
                - last_exploration_event_timestamp.
                - stored_second_run_result.

                Conditions:
                - System is running (not in hardware-level fault).
                - INIT_COMPLETED flag available for IDLE-&gt;EXPLORE.
                - Uses exploration events, planner responses, motion status, and last_exploration_event_type to drive deterministic transitions between mission states.

                RETURN_TO_START handling (clarified with ExecutionState):
                - While in RETURN_TO_START:
                  * Monitor MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus each cycle.
                  * When execution_state == COMPLETED and current_cell == start_cell:
                      - If last_exploration_event_type == EXPLORATION_COMPLETED:
                          - Treat return as successful after full exploration.
                          - Transition to SECOND_RUN (subject to FSM guard).
                      - If last_exploration_event_type == EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT:
                          - Depending on policy, may still allow SECOND_RUN if map sufficient, or transition to COMPLETED with failure; policy defined in AdditionalData but guard in FSM ensures SECOND_RUN requires completion as per LL--RUN--1.2.1.
                  * If execution_state == BLOCKED or EMERGENCY_STOP for longer than configured threshold and planner reports no alternative path, treat as planning/execution failure and transition to COMPLETED.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Invoked exactly once per control loop with period T defined by scheduler (LL--SCHED--1.1.1).
                - EXPLORE behavior: frontier requests and planning requests are limited to at most one per control loop but may be throttled (e.g., only when previous path has been consumed or invalidated).
                - RETURN_TO_START and SECOND_RUN: planning invoked once per entry; replanning invoked when map invalidations arise.
                - All decisions must complete within the control loop budget; mission control logic is O(1) to O(N_frontiers) per cycle, where N_frontiers is bounded by 32 cells in a 4x8 grid.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Mission state is always one of {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - State transitions are deterministic for a given history of events and time.
                - While in COMPLETED, no new motion commands are issued to motion control.
                - While in IDLE, motors remain stopped except for test routines external to this component.
                - Only one of EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, or SECOND_RUN can be active at a time.
                - last_exploration_event_type is updated only when EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT is dequeued and remains latched for the rest of the mission.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning failure in RETURN_TO_START:
                  Trigger: PL_PathPlanningResponse with FAILURE_NO_PATH or FAILURE_TIMEOUT for return-to-start request.
                  Effect: Mission control records return failure, may either:
                    * Transition directly to COMPLETED with MC_SecondRunStatusOutput=FAILURE, or
                    * Remain in RETURN_TO_START and request retry with backoff (implementation policy encoded via AdditionalData).
                - Planning failure in SECOND_RUN:
                  Trigger: PL_PathPlanningResponse with FAILURE_NO_PATH or FAILURE_TIMEOUT for second-run request.
                  Effect: MC_SecondRunStatusOutput=FAILURE; transition to COMPLETED.
                - Exploration timeout:
                  Trigger: EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event prior to EXPLORATION_COMPLETED.
                  Effect: EXPLORE-&gt;RETURN_TO_START, with cause logged as TIMEOUT; last_exploration_event_type set to EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT.
                - Unexpected event in COMPLETED:
                  Any further exploration or planning events are ignored; MC_SecondRunStatusOutput remains latched.
            </Failures>
