                            <Description>
                                Set of frontier cells: UNKNOWN cells that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell.
                                Represented as vector of (row, col).
                                Recomputed:
                                - On demand (MC_FrontierRequest).
                                - Whenever a cell transitions from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED or a wall changes classification, via map-change notifications.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FGM_SelectedTarget</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Single frontier cell chosen as exploration target based on heuristic.
                                Structure:
                                - TargetCell (row, col).
                                - EstimatedTravelTimeMs.
                                - EstimatedNewlyObservableCells.
                                - CompositeHeuristicValue.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Trigger from mission control to update frontier set and provide a new frontier target.
                                Includes: current robot cell, remaining exploration time, and cost profile ID.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries to grid map:
                                - GetCellState(row, col) -&gt; {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                                - GetNeighborCells4(row, col) -&gt; list of valid neighbor indices.
                                - GetWallState between cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>TimeAwarePlanningInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                RemainingTimeMs and NominalCellTraversalDurationMs from time-constraint module.
                                Used to discard frontier candidates whose estimated travel time + mapping overhead exceeds RemainingTimeMs.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_TravelTimeEstimates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Helper interface from path planner used when FGM requests approximate costs to a set of frontier cells without computing full individual paths (e.g., multi-goal heuristics).
                                Encodes estimated traversal times by reusing path cost metric.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Executed in two contexts:
                - On-demand: when MC_FrontierRequest is received within EXPLORE, FGM recomputes the frontier set (if stale) and selects a target.
                - Incremental maintenance: subscribed to grid-map classification-change notifications (CMP--3) and updates cached frontier set whenever a cell state changes from UNKNOWN or walls change, to allow O(1) retrieval during MC_FrontierRequest.
                All operations occur inside the periodic control loop.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Frontier recomputation worst-case: scans 4x8 grid (32 cells) each time; negligible vs control loop period.
                - Target selection heuristic loops over at most N_frontiers &lt;= 32 candidates.
                - Triggered at most once per control loop for target selection; frontier set maintenance can occur multiple times per loop, but in practice limited by sensor update rate and smaller number of cell changes.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Frontier set contains only UNKNOWN cells.
                - Each frontier cell has at least one 4-neighbor classified FREE.
                - Selected target always belongs to current frontier set and satisfies remaining-time constraint.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No frontier cells available:
                  Trigger: FGM_FrontierSet empty.
                  Effect: FGM_SelectedTarget indicates no target; MC interprets this as exploration completion candidate. Exploration-status module will eventually publish EXPLORATION_COMPLETED based on map completeness.
                - Time-limit constraint violation:
                  Trigger: All frontier candidates have estimated travel time + mapping overhead &gt; RemainingTimeMs.
                  Effect: FGM_SelectedTarget reports no feasible targets; MC may continue short movements or immediately rely on exploration timeout event to transition to RETURN_TO_START.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4 LL--MAP--1.1.5 LL--MAP--1.1.6
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--3</ID>
            <Name>Grid Map Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains the in-memory 4x8 grid map and associated wall segments, providing single-threaded access and update mechanisms:
                - Stores cell classification (UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED) and wall segment classification (UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT).
                - Initializes map and start cell.
                - Provides query and update operations.
                - Emits classification-change notifications.
                - Provides map completeness boolean for exploration logic.
                - Enforces immutability rules for classifications within a mission.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Map structure exposed to planning and exploration modules via interface functions:
                                - GetCellState(row, col).
                                - GetWallState(edgeIndex / (row, col, orientation)).
                                - GetNeighbors(row, col) considering map boundaries.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification event issued when a cell or wall segment changes classification.
                                Contains:
                                - Type: {CELL, WALL}.
                                - Indices.
                                - PreviousState and NewState.
                                Consumed by frontier-generation, replanning, and other modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_MapUpdateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Update requests from mapping module: mark cells FREE/BLOCKED and walls PRESENT/ABSENT based on sensor interpretation and pose.
                                Each request includes:
                                - Target indices.
                                - Requested new classification.
                                - Reason (e.g., cell traversed, wall detected).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag indicating whether map is complete:
                                - true: no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains UNKNOWN.
                                - false: otherwise.
                                Sampled by exploration-status module and mission control to decide exploration completion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Init_Request</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Initialization trigger received at system startup to:
                                - Initialize all cells and wall segments to UNKNOWN.
                                - Designate the fixed start cell and set it to FREE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Map initialization at startup:
                  1) Allocate cell array [4][8], initialize each cell state to UNKNOWN.
                  2) Allocate wall arrays for vertical and horizontal walls as per inter-cell wall indexing.
                  3) Mark designated start cell (e.g., (0,0)) as FREE.
                - During each control loop:
                  - Apply queued map update requests from mapping module (ensuring UNKNOWN-&gt;FREE/BLOCKED or UNKNOWN-&gt;PRESENT/ABSENT only).
                  - Trigger classification-change notifications for any changed entries.
                  - Recompute completeness lazily as needed or maintain counters of UNKNOWN cells/walls.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All map operations are performed inside the control loop context (single-threaded), as required by LL--MAP--1.3.7.
                - Worst-case map operations (scanning 32 cells and associated walls) are bounded and fast relative to T.
                - Completeness flag may be recomputed incrementally using maintained counts to ensure O(1) behavior per update.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Every cell state ∈ {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                - Every wall segment state ∈ {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - No cell reverts from FREE/BLOCKED to UNKNOWN and no wall reverts from PRESENT/ABSENT to UNKNOWN within a mission.
                - No cell or wall toggles between FREE/BLOCKED or PRESENT/ABSENT once set (monotonic classification).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Invalid classification transition:
                  Trigger: request to change from FREE/BLOCKED to another value or PRESENT/ABSENT to another value.
                  Handling: reject update and log diagnostic; preserve existing classification.
                - Out-of-range indices:
                  Trigger: requests referencing cells or walls outside 4x8 map.
                  Handling: discard update, log error.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.3.3 LL--MAP--1.3.4 LL--MAP--1.3.5 LL--MAP--1.3.6
                LL--MAP--1.3.7 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--MAP--1.4.3 LL--MAP--1.4.4
                LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--4</ID>
            <Name>Path Planner</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Implements cell-based path planning on the 4x8 grid map:
                - Provides Dijkstra or A* search to compute paths between cells and goal regions.
                - Supports configurable traversal cost parameters for exploration and second run.
                - Handles multiple-goal planning for 2x2 goal regions.
                - Supports replanning on map updates that invalidate current paths.
                - Reports planning failures to mission control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PathPlanningResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning result for a given request:
                                - RequestID.
                                - Status: SUCCESS or specific failure.
                                - Path: ordered list of cells from start to selected goal.
                                - TotalCost and optionally EstimatedTimeMs (TotalCost transformed via cost-to-time mapping).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_PlanningFailureEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Simplified event to indicate no path exists given current map.
                                Used by mission control to trigger alternative behaviors.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathPlanningRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning request specifying:
                                - Mode {EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN}.
                                - Start cell and goal specification (single cell or list of goal cells for goal region).
                                - Traversal cost parameters ID.
                                - Optional limit on max allowed cost.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_MapReadAccess</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Access to grid map functions:
                                - Query cell and wall states to build navigation graph.
                                - Implement 4-connected neighbors only between FREE cells not separated by PRESENT walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Planning invalidation hook:
                                - When map changes mark cells from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED or walls UNKNOWN-&gt;PRESENT that intersect current path, planner flags current path as invalid.
                                - Planner notifies mission control about invalidation via PL_PlanningFailureEvent or dedicated status.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_GoalRegionCostInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Intermediate data shared with goal-region selection:
                                - For each 2x2 FREE candidate region, path cost from start to each cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_GoalCells</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For second run, planner receives the selected goal region cells from goal-region selection module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On each planning request:
                  1) Build search graph implicitly using grid map cell states and wall states.
                  2) Apply Dijkstra or A* depending on configuration:
                     - Node = FREE cell.
                     - Edge exists for orthogonally adjacent FREE cells if there is no PRESENT wall between them.
                     - Edge cost determined from traversal cost model (straight and turn penalties).
                  3) For goal regions, treat each FREE goal cell as a possible terminal node; run multi-goal search or run algorithm once until all goals discovered.
                  4) On success, reconstruct path and compute total cost.
                  5) Map cost to time estimate using nominal cell traversal duration for derived heuristics.
                  6) Return PL_PathPlanningResponse.
                - Replanning:
                  - When GM_ClassificationChangeEvent arrives and current path intersects newly BLOCKED or wall PRESENT segments, invalidate current path and notify mission control.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Path planning executed within control loop but may be limited to one planning run per loop.
                - With 32 cells, worst-case Dijkstra/A* is small; implementation must ensure worst-case search finishes within T, or planning can span multiple loops with incremental expansion.
                - Replanning triggered only when path invalidation occurs to avoid unnecessary computations.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - No path includes BLOCKED cells or crosses PRESENT walls.
                - Edge costs are non-negative.
                - Returned path cost is minimal given the traversal cost model.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No path found:
                  Trigger: search exhausts all reachable cells without reaching any goal.
                  Effect: PL_PathPlanningResponse with Status=FAILURE_NO_PATH; mission control handles this (e.g., abort or alternative behavior).
                - Map inconsistent during planning:
                  Trigger: map changes while planning in progress.
                  Handling: either lock snapshot of map per planning run or restart planning with new map; only consistent snapshots used for final paths.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--PLAN--1.1.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.4 LL--PLAN--1.1.5
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--ENV--3.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--5</ID>
            <Name>Goal Region Identification and Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Determining and selecting the 2x2 goal region after exploration:
                - Identifies all candidate 2x2 regions composed entirely of FREE cells and reachable from start.
                - Requests path costs to each candidate from path planner.
                - Selects region with minimal optimal path cost.
                - Exposes chosen region to second-run planning and mission control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_CandidateRegions</Name>
                            <Description>
                                List of candidate 2x2 FREE regions:
                                - Each candidate: 4 cell indices (row, col) representing the region.
                                - Mark if reachable from start (using info from path planner or BFS).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Read-only snapshot of FREE/BLOCKED cell states to enumerate all 2x2 blocks and check classification.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_GoalRegionSelection</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected goal region:
                                - Set of up to four FREE goal cells.
                                - Region ID and path cost.
                                Provided to planner for second-run fastest path computation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PL_GoalRegionCostInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each candidate region, cost of cheapest path from start cell to any of its 4 cells, using the traversal cost metric.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_SelectedGoalRegionInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Goal region exported to mission control for use in SECOND_RUN:
                                - Region cells.
                                - Chosen target goal cell (may be the one with minimum path cost).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ExplorationCompletedTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event from exploration-status/mission control indicating exploration is complete and goal region identification should execute exactly once.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On exploration completion:
                  1) Obtain map snapshot from grid map.
                  2) Enumerate all possible 2x2 blocks; for each, check all four cells are FREE.
                  3) For each all-FREE block, request path costs via path planner from start to each of the four cells.
                  4) Filter out non-reachable candidates (no path).
                  5) Select candidate whose minimal path cost is smallest.
                  6) Store and publish selected region.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Executed once after map completion detection.
                - With at most (3*7)=21 possible 2x2 blocks and 32 cells, enumeration and cost queries are trivial; must fit within several control loop cycles.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Selected goal region, if any, is reachable from start.
                - Selected region cost is minimal among reachable candidate regions based on traversal cost metric.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No 2x2 FREE reachable region:
                  Trigger: enumeration yields no candidate that is all FREE and reachable.
                  Effect: report failure condition to mission control; second run may be disabled or alternative criteria used (e.g., single goal cell).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--ENV--3.1.1 LL--ENV--3.1.2 LL--PLAN--1.1.3 LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--6</ID>
            <Name>Mapping and Wall Detection Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Uses processed sensor data and pose estimation to update grid map cells and walls:
                - Interprets ultrasonic and infrared readings to detect front and side walls with uncertainty and hysteresis.
                - Executes wall proximity thresholding with hysteresis on ultrasonic data.
                - Generates collision avoidance triggers when trajectory intersects imminent walls.
                - Applies free cell confirmation and blocked cell inference rules.
                - Issues map update requests to grid map.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_MapUpdateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to grid map:
                                - Update wall segment classifications (PRESENT/ABSENT) on appropriate boundaries.
                                - Update cell classifications to FREE or BLOCKED.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellAndWallStates</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current classification around robot:
                                - State of current cell, neighboring cells, and relevant walls.
                                Used for consistent updates and blocked cell inference.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interpreted wall detections relative to current cell:
                                - Flags for front, left, right wall presence.
                                - Estimated wall distances (with uncertainty intervals) in maze coordinates.
                                Used by motion control for avoidance and by pose correction.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_CollisionRiskEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event raised if predicted trajectory intersects a wall within one cell length, triggering avoidance maneuvers in motion control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Filtered sensor data from sensor abstraction and filtering:
                                - Ultrasonic: (distance_cm, timestamp).
                                - IR: left_flag, right_flag, timestamp.
                                All invalid or out-of-range readings already sanitized.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Discrete pose estimate with cell-centered position and heading, plus flag indicating:
                                - AtCellCenter or InTransitionBetweenCells.
                                Used to decide when to update particular walls and cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Read filtered, validated sensor measurements and current pose.
                2) If pose aligned to maze axes within tolerance and at/near cell center:
                   - Use ultrasonic reading to check for front wall:
                     * Compute measurement interval [d-12, d+12] cm.
                     * Compute expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval (based on cell size 17.2 cm and robot radius 5.5 cm, plus wall thickness).
                     * If intervals intersect and past hysteresis thresholds confirm stable detection, mark front wall PRESENT.
                   - Use IR readings:
                     * If left_flag or right_flag active and pose heading within 10° tolerance, infer side wall presence:
                       - Account for 25° sensor mounting angle and 4 cm effective range and project to wall location on left/right boundary of current cell.
                       - Mark corresponding lateral walls PRESENT.
                3) If robot transitions between cell centers without collisions:
                   - Mark traversed cells as FREE once verified by sensor consistency checks.
                4) Apply wall proximity thresholding:
                   - Use configurable upper/lower thresholds on filtered ultrasonic distance to determine wall vs free.
                   - Maintain hysteresis state per direction to avoid flip-flopping.
                5) For any present wall between current and neighbor cell, mark neighbor cell BLOCKED and ensure no motion commands target it.
                6) Issue map update requests accordingly.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Invoked once per control loop after sensor filtering, before grid-map updates are applied.
                - Computations are simple algebra and local reasoning around at most a few walls; must complete within T.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Free cell confirmation only after successful traversal without collision and no conflicting evidence requiring N consecutive contradictions.
                - Blocked cell inference always consistent with wall segment state PRESENT.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Conflicting sensor data vs map:
                  Trigger: new sensor readings indicate a wall where map indicates FREE or ABSENT, but do not satisfy N consecutive readings threshold.
                  Handling: flagged as potential sensor error; map left unchanged until N readings accumulate.
                - Pose misalignment &gt; tolerance:
                  Trigger: robot heading deviates &gt;10° from maze axes.
                  Effect: IR-based side wall inference suppressed until pose is corrected.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.2.2 LL--MAP--1.2.3 LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.4.3 LL--MAP--1.4.4
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1 LL--INTERF--3.3.1 LL--INTERF--3.4.1
                LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--ENV--1.3.1 LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--7</ID>
            <Name>Sensor Abstraction and Filtering Layer</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Wraps raw sensor APIs and provides normalized, filtered sensor data:
                - Calls ultrasonic_get_distance and IR status functions at control loop frequency.
                - Detects and handles invalid/out-of-range sensor readings.
                - Applies temporal filtering (moving average/median) to reduce noise.
                - Provides unified ultrasonic and IR measurement structures to mapping and reliability modules.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SampledSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Raw per-cycle data from sensors:
                                - Ultrasonic distance (float cm).
                                - IR left/right flags (uint8_t to boolean).
                                - Timestamps.
                                Provided immediately after acquisition to filtering logic.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Tick from scheduler at frequency matching configured sensor sampling rate.
                                Used to ensure one sampling per iteration and enforce jitter constraints.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SamplingConfigFromReliability</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration from Reliability/Safety module specifying:
                                - sampling_frequency_hz f with 10 ≤ f ≤ 50; default f = 20.
                                - maximum allowed jitter (e.g., ±10% of T).
                                SAL uses f to confirm that control loop period T matches requested sampling rate.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_CurrentTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Timestamp for each tick (ms); used by SAL to measure actual inter-sample interval and log excessive jitter if detected.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Normalized and filtered sensor data:
                                - Ultrasonic: (filteredDistance_cm, timestamp, valid_flag).
                                - IR: (filteredLeftFlag, filteredRightFlag, timestamp, valid_flag).
                                Filtering uses configured sampling rate (10–50 Hz, default 20 Hz) and temporal filtering method.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SensorAvailabilityStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag indicating that at least one valid (non-invalid) ultrasonic distance and both IR readings have been successfully acquired at least once since mission start.
                                Used by mission control to determine exploration start condition.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RawUltrasonicApi</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interface to ultrasonic_get_distance(), returning raw float distance or specific error/saturation codes.
                                SAL is responsible for interpreting invalid codes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RawIrApi</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Interfaces to infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status().
                                Returns uint8_t for each sensor interpreted as binary detection flags.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) On Sched_ControlLoopTick, SAL samples sensors exactly once:
                   - Call ultrasonic_get_distance(), infrared_get_dsl_status(), infrared_get_dsr_status().
                2) Validate that effective sampling frequency f satisfies 10 Hz ≤ f ≤ 50 Hz and approximate f ≈ 1/T from scheduler. SAL monitors actual inter-sample intervals using SCHED_CurrentTime:
                   - If jitter (difference between actual and expected interval) exceeds configured tolerance, SAL logs a jitter warning but continues operation; it does not change behavior of delivered values.
                3) Check for invalid values (negative distances, NaN, saturation codes):
                   - Replace invalid ultrasonic values with "no obstacle" default (e.g., beyond maze size plus uncertainty) and set valid_flag = false for mapping decisions.
                   - IR invalid values treated as no obstacle (flag false) or flagged per configuration.
                4) Push readings into fixed-length buffers (size determined by filter window) and compute filtered values (moving average or median).
                5) Compose normalized structures with filtered values, uncertainty interval (for ultrasonic) and current timestamp.
                6) Update SensorAvailabilityStatus if all required sensors have delivered at least one valid reading.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sampling exactly once per control loop iteration, at frequency in [10, 50] Hz.
                - Timing jitter limited by scheduler; SAL monitors jitter via SCHED_CurrentTime and configuration from CMP--16, and logs if tolerance is exceeded.
                - Filtering operations O(windowSize) with small window sizes (e.g., 3–5 samples).
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - SAL never forwards raw invalid values to mapping or planning modules; it always marks them invalid or substitutes safe defaults.
                - Filtered data is always defined (either from valid readings or safe defaults).
                - Sampling rate f remains within configured range [10,50] Hz, with default 20 Hz, as enforced jointly by scheduler and reliability configuration.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Persistent invalid ultrasonic reading:
                  Handling: maintain default "no obstacle" reading while flagging sensor degradation; mapping may rely more heavily on IR or map data.
                - Loss of IR data:
                  Handling: treat IR as inactive (no obstacle) but rely on ultrasonic and map to avoid collisions; log error.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.1.2 LL--INTERF--2.1.1 LL--INTERF--3.1.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--8</ID>
            <Name>Motion Control and Collision Avoidance</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Converts high-level path and motion primitives into motor_set commands with safety:
                - Executes cell-center motion primitives based on differential drive kinematics and cell geometry.
                - Enforces speed limitations, rate limiting, and emergency stop behavior.
                - Performs wall avoidance maneuvers when mapping reports imminent collisions.
                - Supports different speed profiles for exploration, return-to-start, and second run.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status of path execution, initiated by Motion Controller:
                                Fields:
                                - execution_state: {IDLE, EXECUTING, BLOCKED, COMPLETED, EMERGENCY_STOP}.
                                - mode: {EXPLORATION, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN}.
                                - current_cell: (row, col).
                                - reached_goal_flag: bool, true when final path cell reached.
                                - error_code: optional (e.g., PATH_INVALID, COLLISION_ABORTED).
                                Mission Control receives this as MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus and uses it for state transitions and replanning.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion instruction from mission control including:
                                - Path (sequence of cells) or next cell target.
                                - Speed profile.
                                - Safety constraints.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EM_StopCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Conceptual: internal invocation of motor_set(0,0) when emergency conditions occur.
                                Indicates emergency stop activation for logging and status reporting.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to monitor distance to obstacles for emergency-stop decisions based on configured emergency threshold and stopping distance.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Motion_MotorCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation of motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) with speeds in [0,100].
                                Enforced to be at most once per control loop, respecting rate limiting on speed increments.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Ensures motor commands are synchronized with control loop period T and updates internal timers for motion primitive durations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Motion_AvoidanceStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notifies mapping/mission control when avoidance maneuvers are in progress or completed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to predict trajectory-wall intersections within one cell length and trigger avoidance maneuvers before collision.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_CollisionRiskEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Direct event indicating imminent collision within one cell length; triggers avoidance or emergency stop.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Read current MC_MotionCommand, SAL_FilteredSensorData, and MM_WallDetectionResult.
                2) If emergency condition:
                   - If any sensor indicates obstacle closer than emergency threshold &lt; nominal stopping distance (based on current speed and uncertainty):
                     * Immediately call motor_set(0,0).
                     * Set internal execution_state to EMERGENCY_STOP.
                     * Emit MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus with execution_state == EMERGENCY_STOP.
                     * Do not resume movement until new safe path or motion command is provided.
                3) Else if MM_CollisionRiskEvent raised:
                   - Plan short avoidance maneuver (e.g., stop + in-place turn, or arc turn) such that:
                     * Robot center trajectory remains within FREE cells (or at least within regions that do not intersect cells classified as BLOCKED or cross PRESENT walls, when inflated by robot radius + margin M).
                     * The motion primitive does not require crossing any PRESENT wall boundary defined in the grid map.
                     * Robot footprint plus clearance M does not intersect any wall (geometric check per DAT--2).
                     * Maneuver maintains or restores progress towards mission goal where feasible (e.g., re-aligns path around obstacle and returns to planned corridor).
                4) If executing a cell-center motion primitive:
                   - Use differential drive kinematics with control-loop period to incrementally move between cell centers or rotate to discrete headings.
                   - Ensure that the nominal primitive path (including any applied avoidance offsets) is contained within FREE cells defined by the map and never crosses a PRESENT wall boundary.
                   - Enforce speed limits:
                     * ExplorationSpeed &lt;= MaxSafeSpeedExploration.
                     * SecondRunSpeed &lt;= MaxSafeSpeedSecondRun &lt; hardware limit and derived from safety constraints.
                5) Before calling motor_set:
                   - Apply rate limiting to speed increments between consecutive cycles.
                6) Issue one motor_set per cycle with computed speeds.
                7) Update MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus each cycle with current execution_state, current_cell, and flags; set execution_state to COMPLETED only when final path cell is reached without violation of BLOCKED/PRESENT constraints.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Called once per control loop after mission control and path planning decisions.
                - Kinematic integration and collision checks use current T or measured cycle duration.
                - Emergency stop and avoidance decisions must be computed within one loop so that robot can stop within safe distance given sampling rate and uncertainties.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Rate of change of motor_set speeds per control cycle does not exceed configured maximum per wheel.
                - Commanded speeds never exceed configured safety maximum computed from sampling rate, emergency distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
                - Any commanded trajectory (including avoidance maneuvers) does not intentionally enter cells classified as BLOCKED and does not require crossing boundaries between cells where wall state is PRESENT.
                - Active path and any local deviation for avoidance remain within geometric envelope that ensures clearance ≥ (robot_radius + M) from all PRESENT walls.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Emergency stop:
                  Trigger: obstacle detected within emergency distance.
                  Effect: immediate motor_set(0,0); path execution aborted; MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus updated with execution_state == EMERGENCY_STOP; higher-level logic may replan.
                - Inability to find avoidance maneuver:
                  Trigger: all nearby candidate maneuvers would violate minimum clearance M or require crossing PRESENT walls.
                  Effect: remain stopped, report BLOCKED/EMERGENCY_STOP via MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus and rely on higher-level replanning or manual recovery.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.4
                LL--RUN--1.1.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1 LL--INTERF--1.2.2
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2 LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.2
                LL--MAP--1.4.4 LL--PLAN--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--9</ID>
            <Name>Pose Estimation Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains discrete cell-level pose estimate:
                - Integrates differential drive kinematics over control loop periods.
                - Estimates current cell index (row, col) and discrete heading aligned with maze axes.
                - Corrects accumulated errors using detected walls and alignment.
                - Detects transitions between cell centers and notifies mapping module.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Current pose estimate including:
                                - Cell indices (row, col).
                                - Discrete heading index ∈ {NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, WEST}.
                                - Continuous pose (x,y,θ) in maze frame if needed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>CellCenterEntryEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event fired when pose crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center.
                                Contains new cell index and direction of motion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides duration T or measured cycle duration used for integration of motor commands.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseForMotionControl</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Detail of continuous pose and heading used by motion control to determine progress along primitives.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotionCommandedSpeeds</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Last-issued motor_set speeds for left and right wheels; used to integrate motion via kinematics.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PoseAlignedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag to mapping indicating when pose has been snapped to maze axes and is reliable for wall mapping decisions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MM_WallDetectionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to correct pose when walls indicate proximity to known cell boundaries; align orientation and position to nearest consistent cell center.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Per control loop:
                1) Use last cycle's motor speed commands and loop duration T to integrate differential drive kinematics:
                   - Update continuous pose (x,y,θ).
                2) Map continuous pose to discrete cell indices using grid coordinate system and cell dimension 17.2 cm.
                3) If near theoretical cell center and heading near axis-aligned directions:
                   - Snap heading to nearest axis orientation.
                   - Snap position to nearest cell center consistent with wall locations.
                4) Detect cell center transitions by comparing previous and current discrete cell indices.
                   - Emit CellCenterEntryEvent when crossing occurs.
                5) Provide PoseEstimate to consumers.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updates once per control loop after motion command is known.
                - Needs to complete before mapping and mission control use updated pose.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Discrete heading always one of four axis-aligned states.
                - PoseEstimate always maps to a valid cell within [0..3][0..7].
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Large discrepancy between pose and walls:
                  Handling: if no consistent cell center matches wall observations, keep last valid discrete pose and flag degraded pose quality for mapping.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--POSE--1.1.1 LL--POSE--1.1.2 LL--POSE--1.1.3
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.2.1
                LL--MAP--1.3.2 LL--MAP--1.2.1 LL--MAP--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--10</ID>
            <Name>Scheduler and Initialization</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides main control loop timing and initialization signaling:
                - Implements periodic control loop at configurable period T.
                - Coordinates execution order: sensor sampling, map update, mission control, planning, motion control.
                - After init, raises INIT_COMPLETED indication.
                - Ensures sensor sampling rate equals control loop frequency.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Sched_ControlLoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Clock tick for each control loop iteration:
                                - Used by SAL, motion control, pose estimation to advance state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_Config</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration of sampling rate within [10, 50] Hz, default 20 Hz, used to determine T.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>InitCompletedFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Binary flag/event set after all hardware and software initialization routines have been executed successfully.
                                Mission control reads this to leave IDLE state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>HardwareInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Results of hardware initialization routines.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - At startup:
                  1) Run hardware and software initialization routines.
                  2) Initialize grid map, pose, sensors, motion control configurations.
                  3) Set INIT_COMPLETED flag.
                - Periodic control loop (every T):
                  1) Emit Sched_ControlLoopTick.
                  2) Acquire sensor readings via SAL.
                  3) Update grid map via mapping and map module.
                  4) Update mission control state machine.
                  5) Trigger path planning for active state.
                  6) Execute motion control (issuing motor_set once per loop).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Control loop frequency equals configured sampling rate.
                - Jitter bounds derived from LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 must be met; scheduler ensures stable T.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Exactly one pass through the ordered steps per control loop iteration.
                - No concurrent execution of map access functions (single-threaded model).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Failure in initialization step:
                  Effect: INIT_COMPLETED not set; mission control remains in IDLE, robot not moving.
                - Timer overrun:
                  If a loop iteration exceeds T, scheduler records overrun and may extend next period or skip non-critical tasks like logging.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.1.1 LL--INTERF--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--11</ID>
            <Name>Exploration Status and Time Limit Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Monitors map completeness and exploration time to emit exploration status events:
                - Tracks elapsed exploration time.
                - Checks grid map completeness flag.
                - Emits EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events via system event queue.
                - Provides remaining exploration time to time-aware planning.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_MapCompletenessQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query of boolean map complete flag each control loop or at configured intervals.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessFlag</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean indicating whether map is complete.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ExplorationEvents</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queue entries created when:
                                - Map completeness changes from false to true (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED).
                                - Elapsed exploration time exceeds 5 minutes (EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RemainingExplorationTimeInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                ElapsedTimeMs and RemainingTimeMs (5 min - ElapsedTimeMs) available to mission control and exploration modules.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_StateBroadcast</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Used to identify when EXPLORE starts/stops for time tracking (elapsed time measured only while in exploration phase or from exploration start as defined).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>TimeAwarePlanningInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Remaining exploration time and nominal cell traversal duration parameter exposed for frontier target selection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>NominalTraversalParam</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configurable parameter (ms per cell) used to convert path steps into estimated traversal times.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On entering EXPLORE:
                  - Record exploration start time (mission time).
                - Each control loop:
                  1) Compute elapsed exploration time from start time.
                  2) If elapsed &gt;= 5 minutes:
                     - Emit EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event exactly once.
                  3) If GM_MapCompletenessFlag is true and not yet signaled:
                     - Emit EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event exactly once.
                  4) Update RemainingExplorationTimeInfo for other modules.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Event checks happen once per control loop.
                - Uses scheduler-provided mission time or tick counts to compute elapsed time accurately.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and one EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event per mission.
                - RemainingTimeMs never negative; clamped at zero.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Time base failure (no time information):
                  Handling: treat as no remaining time; likely cause immediate timeout and safe return behavior.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.6 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>
    </Components>

    <StateMachines version="2">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Keep motors stopped (no MC_MotionCommand).
                        - Monitor INIT_COMPLETED and SensorAvailabilityStatus flags.
                        - Initialize exploration-related timers and flags upon future exit.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Periodically request frontier targets from CMP--2.
                        - Send MC_PathPlanningRequest to CMP--4 for selected frontier cell.
                        - If path available, issue MC_MotionCommand in exploration speed profile to CMP--8.
                        - Monitor ExplorationEvents and pose to detect exploration completion/timeout.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke return-to-start service: request path from current cell to start cell.
                        - Command motion control to execute return path.
                        - Monitor ReturnToStartStatus and MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus for completion or failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Request fastest path from start cell to selected goal region with time-optimized traversal cost.
                        - Command motion control to execute path with higher speed profile respecting safety.
                        - Monitor second run execution status to derive success/failure.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Cease issuing new MC_MotionCommand (motors left stopped by motion control).
                        - Maintain final second-run status in MC_SecondRunStatusOutput for external reporting.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        INIT_COMPLETED indication present AND SensorAvailabilityStatus is true, both sampled within control loop.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No critical errors in initialization.
                        - Map initialized with start cell set to FREE.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Reset exploration timers and elapsed time counters.
                        - Initialize exploration modules (frontier generation, exploration-status).
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event OR
                        - Receipt of EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event from exploration-status module, whichever occurs first.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Current motion commands are safe to stop or replan.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop issuing further frontier requests.
                        - Issue return-to-start path planning request from current cell to start cell.
                        - Set internal last_exploration_event_type to EXPLORATION_COMPLETED or EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT accordingly.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - ReturnToStartStatus indicates REACHED_START or MCtrl_PathExecutionStatus.execution_state == COMPLETED with current_cell == start_cell.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Robot pose at start cell (verified by pose estimate and possibly small tolerance).
                        - Start cell is FREE in map.
                        - last_exploration_event_type == EXPLORATION_COMPLETED (i.e., exploration terminated due to completeness, not timeout-only), as stored in Mission Control internal status.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Request goal region identification/selection if not already done.
                        - Request fastest path plan (SECOND_RUN mode).
                        - Initialize MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to RUNNING.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        ReturnToStartStatus indicates PLANNING_FAILURE or ABORTED_COLLISION and no alternative route available.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Policy: mission ends if robot cannot return safely.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to FAILURE.
                        - Ensure motion commands are stopped.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == SUCCESS_REACHED_GOAL OR
                        - SecondRunExecutionStatus == FAILURE_COLLISION OR
                        - Planning failure for fastest path.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        None beyond trigger; any terminal status ends mission.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Latch MC_SecondRunStatusOutput to SUCCESS or FAILURE depending on reported status.
                        - Stop issuing path execution commands to motion control.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        Optional direct mission abort if unrecoverable system fault occurs during exploration (e.g., hardware failure).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - System fault flag set.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop all motion; set mission status to FAILURE.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.3 LL--MAP--1.1.4
                LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--MAP--1.5.2
                LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--RUN--1.1.2
                LL--RUN--1.2.1 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--RUN--1.2.3 LL--RUN--1.2.4 LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>
    </StateMachines>

    <AdditionalData version="2">
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--1</ID>
            <Content>
                Enumeration and Core Data Definitions:

                1) Grid Map States
                - enum CellState { CELL_UNKNOWN = 0, CELL_FREE = 1, CELL_BLOCKED = 2 };
                - enum WallState { WALL_UNKNOWN = 0, WALL_PRESENT = 1, WALL_ABSENT = 2 };

                Grid storage:
                - CellState cells[4][8];
                - Horizontal walls between (row, col) and (row+1, col):
                  WallState hWalls[3][8];
                - Vertical walls between (row, col) and (row, col+1):
                  WallState vWalls[4][7];

                Coordinate convention (example):
                - Row 0, Col 0 is start cell at specified corner as per HL environment.
                All modules must consistently use this indexing.

                2) Mission and Execution State
                - enum MissionState { MS_IDLE, MS_EXPLORE, MS_RETURN_TO_START, MS_SECOND_RUN, MS_COMPLETED };
                - enum ExecutionState {
                      EXEC_STATE_IDLE,
                      EXEC_STATE_EXECUTING,
                      EXEC_STATE_BLOCKED,
                      EXEC_STATE_COMPLETED,
                      EXEC_STATE_EMERGENCY_STOP
                  };

                3) Path Request and Planner Status
                - enum PathRequestType {
                      PATH_REQ_EXPLORATION_TO_FRONTIER,
                      PATH_REQ_RETURN_TO_START,
                      PATH_REQ_SECOND_RUN_TO_GOAL
                  };
                - enum PlannerStatus { PL_SUCCESS, PL_FAILURE_NO_PATH, PL_FAILURE_TIMEOUT, PL_INVALID_GOAL };

                4) Second Run Status
                - enum SecondRunResult {
                      SR_NOT_STARTED,
                      SR_RUNNING,
                      SR_SUCCESS,
                      SR_FAILURE,
                      SR_ABORTED_TIMEOUT,
                      SR_ABORTED_COLLISION
                  };

                5) Exploration Events and Initialization Status
                - enum ExplorationEventType {
                      EXPLORATION_EVENT_NONE = 0,
                      EXPLORATION_COMPLETED,
                      EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT
                  };

                - enum InitStatus {
                      INIT_PENDING = 0,
                      INIT_COMPLETED_OK
                  };

                6) Sensor Validity
                If represented as enumeration instead of bool:
                - enum SensorValidity { SENSOR_INVALID = 0, SENSOR_VALID = 1 };

                SAL shall map valid_flag bools consistently to this semantic (true == SENSOR_VALID).

                7) Event Types for Event Queue
                (Used with DAT--7)
                - enum EventType {
                      EVT_NONE = 0,
                      EVT_EXPLORATION_COMPLETED,
                      EVT_EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT,
                      EVT_PATH_INVALIDATED,
                      EVT_RETURN_COMPLETED,
                      EVT_SECOND_RUN_COMPLETED
                  };
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1 LL--MAP--1.4.1 LL--MAP--1.4.2 LL--ENV--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.4.1
                LL--MAP--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.1 LL--PLAN--1.1.5 LL--RUN--1.2.4 LL--RUN--1.2.5
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--INIT--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--2</ID>
            <Content>
                Traversal Cost Model Parameters:
                - Define cost units such that:
                  baseStraightCost = 1.0 per move between adjacent FREE cells with no turn.
                  turnPenalty = configurable &gt;= 0 for turns between edges (e.g., 0.5).
                - Exploration profile:
                  - Emphasize information gain while maintaining reasonable path length; keep baseStraightCost small, turnPenalty modest.
                - Second-run profile:
                  - Set parameters corresponding to estimated travel time:
                    costPerStraightCell = cellLength / nominalSpeed.
                    costPerTurn = extra time to decelerate, turn, accelerate.
                - Cost computation:
                  For each path:
                    TotalCost = sum(edgeCosts) where edgeCost = baseStraightCost (+turnPenalty when heading changes).
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.1.5 LL--RUN--1.2.2 LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--3</ID>
            <Content>
                Time-Aware Planning and Nominal Cell Traversal Duration:
                - Configuration parameter:
                  uint32_t nominalCellTraversalMs; // default derived from measured robot speed at exploration speed.
                - Remaining exploration time:
                  remainingTimeMs = max(0, explorationTimeLimitMs - elapsedExplorationMs).
                - Frontier feasibility test:
                  For candidate frontier at distance N_cells from current cell:
                    estTravelMs = N_cells * nominalCellTraversalMs;
                    estMappingOverheadMs = nominalCellTraversalMs; // simple fixed overhead.
                    If estTravelMs + estMappingOverheadMs &gt; remainingTimeMs, discard candidate.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.2 LL--MAP--1.5.3 LL--MAP--1.1.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--4</ID>
            <Content>
                Ultrasonic Uncertainty and Clearance Checks:
                - Ultrasonic measurement model:
                  Each distance reading d_cm is expanded to [d_cm - 12, d_cm + 12] cm interval.
                - Robot model:
                  Radius R = 5.5 cm.
                  Wall thickness ~1.6 cm.
                  Cell size L = 17.2 cm.
                - Expected center-to-wall distance for front wall when centered in cell:
                  approxDistance = L/2 + wallThickness/2 ≈ 8.6 + 0.8 = 9.4 cm (approximate; derived precisely in implementation).
                - Clearance margin M:
                  Configurable M &gt; 0 cm, e.g., 2–5 cm; planned trajectories ensure robot center stays at least R + M away from any wall boundary.
                - Emergency stop threshold:
                  Derived from maximum speed, stopping distance, and uncertainty interval; ensures robot can stop before wall even in worst-case measurement error.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1 LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--ENV--1.3.1
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.2 LL--MAP--1.2.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--5</ID>
            <Content>
                Sensor Filtering and Consistency Parameters:
                - Sampling frequency:
                  configurable in [10, 50] Hz; default 20 Hz.
                  controlLoopPeriod T = 1 / samplingFrequency.
                - Filter windows:
                  ultrasonicMovingAverageWindow = 3–5 samples.
                  IRmovingAverageOrDebounceWindow = 2–3 samples.
                - Consistency threshold N for changing map entries from FREE/ABSENT to BLOCKED/PRESENT:
                  integer N ∈ [2, 10], default 3.
                  Implementation: maintain counters per cell/wall; only change classification when N consecutive readings indicate a change.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--6</ID>
            <Content>
                Motion Primitive Specification:
                - Straight move primitive:
                  Move from one cell center to adjacent in direction of current discrete heading.
                  Steps:
                  1) Compute distance to travel = cellLength (17.2 cm).
                  2) Compute required duration based on exploration or second-run speed (cm/s).
                  3) Execute repeated motor_set commands with equal left/right speeds for computed number of control loop cycles.
                - Turn in place primitive:
                  Rotate by ±90° or 180° to align with maze axis.
                  Use differential drive kinematics to determine wheel speeds and duration for desired angle based on robot geometry.
                - Arc turn primitive for avoidance:
                  Use left/right speeds with appropriate ratio to follow circular arc of radius &gt;= R + M to maintain clearance from walls, while ensuring that the arc path remains entirely within FREE cells and does not cross PRESENT wall boundaries according to the grid map.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2 LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1 LL--MAP--1.2.4 LL--ENV--1.2.1 LL--RELIAB--1.1.1
                LL--MAP--1.4.4 LL--PLAN--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>

        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--7</ID>
            <Content>
                Event Queue for Exploration and Mission Events:
                - Data structure:
                  Circular buffer of fixed size (e.g., 16 entries) storing:
                  struct Event { EventType type; uint32_t timestamp; EventPayload payload; };
                - Supported event types include:
                  EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT, PATH_INVALIDATED, RETURN_COMPLETED, SECOND_RUN_COMPLETED.
                - Usage:
                  - Modules (e.g., exploration-status) enqueue events.
                  - Mission control dequeues and processes all available events each control loop.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.5.1 LL--RUN--1.1.1 LL--MAP--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
    </AdditionalData>
</Design>
