    <Implementation>
        <FindingID>Design--1--5</FindingID>
        <Explanation>
            The interface topology between the Path Planner (CMP--4) and Motion Controller (CMP--8) has been clarified to reflect that they do not directly exchange messages; all Path Planner interaction is via Mission Control.

            Changes:
            - In the previous version, CMP--8 had a conceptual notion that it might &quot;receive&quot; PL_PathPlanningResponse indirectly via Mission Control, and CMP--4’s commentary hinted at optional MC interaction. This could be misread as a direct connection.
            - In the updated design:
              * CMP--4 only lists CMP--1 (Mission Control), CMP--3 (Grid Map), and CMP--5 (Goal Region module) as connected components.
              * CMP--8 only communicates with CMP--1, CMP--7, CMP--10, and CMP--6.
              * No ConnectedComponent between CMP--4 and CMP--8 exists; all paths are: CMP--1 &lt;-&gt; CMP--4 and CMP--1 &lt;-&gt; CMP--8.

            The description of PP_PathPlanningResponse in CMP--4 and MC_MotionCommand in CMP--1 makes it explicit that Mission Control mediates planner results to Motion Controller. This corresponds to the first option in the proposed solution.
        </Explanation>
    </Implementation>

    <Implementation>
        <FindingID>Design--1--6</FindingID>
        <Explanation>
            The Motion Controller’s behavior and invariants have been refined so that any local avoidance maneuver is explicitly constrained to remain within FREE cells and not cross PRESENT walls, consistent with mapping and planning requirements.

            Changes:
            - In CMP--8 Execution:
              * Step 3 describing avoidance maneuvers has been expanded to state:
                - The robot center trajectory must remain within FREE cells (or areas that do not intersect BLOCKED cells or PRESENT walls when inflated by robot radius plus safety margin M).
                - Avoidance primitives must not require crossing any PRESENT wall boundary.
            - Step 4 has been clarified to say that the nominal primitive path (including applied avoidance offsets) is contained within FREE cells and never crosses PRESENT wall boundaries.
            - In CMP--8 Invariants:
              * New invariants were added:
                - &quot;Any commanded trajectory (including avoidance maneuvers) does not intentionally enter cells classified as BLOCKED and does not require crossing boundaries between cells where wall state is PRESENT.&quot;
                - &quot;Active path and any local deviation for avoidance remain within geometric envelope that ensures clearance ≥ (robot_radius + M) from all PRESENT walls.&quot;

            DAT--6 (Motion Primitive Specification) has also been updated to explicitly state that arc turn primitives for avoidance must remain within FREE cells and not cross PRESENT walls.

            These changes make the relationship between global planner guarantees and local avoidance explicit and traceable to LL--MAP--1.4.4 and LL--PLAN--1.1.1.
        </Explanation>
    </Implementation>

    <Implementation>
        <FindingID>Design--1--7</FindingID>
        <Explanation>
            CMP--7 (Sensor Abstraction and Filtering Layer) has been extended to clearly incorporate the sampling rate and jitter requirements from LL--RELIAB--1.2.1 into its execution behavior and timing.

            Changes:
            - In CMP--7 ConnectedComponents:
              * A Receive signal &quot;SamplingConfigFromReliability&quot; from the reliability/safety module is now defined, specifying:
                - sampling_frequency_hz f with 10 ≤ f ≤ 50, default 20 Hz.
                - maximum allowed jitter.
              * A Receive signal &quot;SCHED_CurrentTime&quot; from the scheduler is defined to provide timestamps for jitter measurement.
            - In CMP--7 Execution:
              * Explicit statements were added that:
                - SAL samples sensors exactly once per Sched_ControlLoopTick.
                - SAL verifies that the effective sampling frequency satisfies 10 Hz ≤ f ≤ 50 Hz and uses SCHED_CurrentTime to monitor inter-sample interval and log jitter violations.
            - In CMP--7 Timing:
              * Timing now explicitly states that SAL monitors jitter according to the tolerance provided and logs but does not distort the delivered measurements.

            This makes the handling of sampling rate and jitter explicit, aligning the design with LL--RELIAB--1.2.1.
        </Explanation>
    </Implementation>

